What a way to go

commentary: Boult to Faheem Ashraf, 5 runs full toss and straying down leg, Ashraf gets a shot away, and they look for three. The first throw is wayward, and the backing up is poor too. They have actually run FIVE here! Sums up the effort from New Zealand today

commentary: Ferguson to Asif Ali, OUT TIMBER! Full, straight, and fast. You miss, I hit, he seems to say, and he walks the talk. Fourth wicket for Ferguson. Why Latham didn't turn to him earlier, we would not know, but perhaps that has made the critical difference between allowing Pakistan to post a winning total and not?

commentary: Ferguson to Hasan Ali, OUT short ball and that's a FIVER for Ferguson! Intelligent lengths and changes in pace, and Lockie Ferguson gets another wicket, as the short ball is whacked by Hasan only in the air on the onside, where Worker does the rest. This is still a fine total by Pakistan, as they finish at 279 for 8. That's 11 more than what they got batting first the last time they clinched a bilateral series against New Zealand in February 2011.

commentary: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Munro, OUT Afridi, you beauty! This is a terrific ball, which storms through the gate of Munro. Fuller than a good length, Shaheen lands this on the seam, jags back in, breaches the weak defences of Munro. This is the reason why he has been fast-tracked to the Test squad, despite playing only two first-class games so far. He's a special talent. Isn't he?
